WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.679 --> 00:00:03.540
Kenyon: "Since Lot was afraid
to stay in Zoar.

2
00:00:03.654 --> 00:00:06.728
he and his two daughters
settled in the hill country.

3
00:00:06.792 --> 00:00:09.093
where he lived in a cave.

4
00:00:09.173 --> 00:00:11.532
The firstborn said
to the younger...

5
00:00:12.049 --> 00:00:14.004
'Our father is getting old.

6
00:00:14.091 --> 00:00:16.239
and there is not a man
in the land

7
00:00:16.314 --> 00:00:20.706
to have intercourse with us
as is the custom everywhere.

8
00:00:21.545 --> 00:00:22.586
Come.

9
00:00:22.976 --> 00:00:27.360
Let us ply our father with
wine and then lie with him.

10
00:00:27.434 --> 00:00:31.989
hat we may ensure posterity
by our father.'

11
00:00:32.467 --> 00:00:35.955
So that night. they plied
their father with wine."

12
00:00:36.026 --> 00:00:37.257
[ Insects chirping ]

13
00:00:37.321 --> 00:00:40.818
"And the firstborn went in
and lay with her father.

14
00:00:41.053 --> 00:00:43.804
The next day. the firstborn
said to the younger.

15
00:00:43.938 --> 00:00:48.594
'Let us ply him
with wine again tonight.

16
00:00:49.352 --> 00:00:53.817
And then you go in
and lie with him.'

17
00:00:54.429 --> 00:00:59.616
So that night. too. they plied
their father with wine.

18
00:01:00.246 --> 00:01:02.177
And then the younger one
went in

19
00:01:02.969 --> 00:01:04.904
and lay with her father.

20
00:01:05.841 --> 00:01:09.441
And so it was that
the two daughters of Lot

21
00:01:09.524 --> 00:01:11.867
became pregnant
by their father."

22
00:01:12.403 --> 00:01:18.031
And thus. Lord. we maketh
your word our command!

23
00:01:18.133 --> 00:01:19.505
All: Amen!

24
00:01:21.308 --> 00:01:23.479
♪ down to the river to pray ♪

25
00:01:23.633 --> 00:01:27.153
♪ studying about
that good old way ♪

26
00:01:27.301 --> 00:01:30.682
♪ and who shall wear
that starry crown ♪

27
00:01:30.751 --> 00:01:34.899
♪ good Lord. show me the way ♪

28
00:01:35.018 --> 00:01:38.979
♪ oh. sisters. let's go down ♪

29
00:01:39.089 --> 00:01:41.060
♪ let's go down ♪

30
00:01:41.139 --> 00:01:42.606
♪ come on down ♪

31
00:01:42.932 --> 00:01:46.749
♪ oh. sisters. let's go down ♪

32
00:01:46.871 --> 00:01:50.809
♪ down to the river to pray ♪

33
00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:54.269
♪ as I went down in the river
to pray ♪

34
00:01:54.346 --> 00:01:55.926
Woman: Dearly beloved.
we are gathered here

35
00:01:55.997 --> 00:01:59.213
in the sight of God
and in the face of this family

36
00:01:59.340 --> 00:02:01.199
to join together this--

37
00:02:01.357 --> 00:02:02.826
[ Woman gasps.
people murmuring ]

38
00:02:07.662 --> 00:02:09.109
[ Glass breaking ]

39
00:02:11.966 --> 00:02:13.849
[ Women screaming ]

40
00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:21.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

41
00:02:22.621 --> 00:02:24.228
[ Screaming intensifies ]

42
00:02:24.835 --> 00:02:26.354
Sync and corrections by n17t01
www.addic7ed.com

43
00:02:29.396 --> 00:02:32.622
_

44
00:02:33.661 --> 00:02:36.889
What do you feel like--
Italian. Thai?

45
00:02:37.618 --> 00:02:39.167
Are we really gonna do this?

46
00:02:39.352 --> 00:02:40.926
Do what?
I'm hungry.

47
00:02:41.825 --> 00:02:43.099
Not talk about it.

48
00:02:43.206 --> 00:02:44.816
I'll probably get turned down.

49
00:02:46.024 --> 00:02:48.205
The trial--
nobody gets in this thing.

50
00:02:48.279 --> 00:02:49.027
It's false hope.

51
00:02:49.099 --> 00:02:50.031
Did you hear
what the doctor said?

52
00:02:50.095 --> 00:02:51.551
I mean.
were you even listening?

53
00:02:51.721 --> 00:02:53.288
I mean.
he said the prognosis is--

54
00:02:54.440 --> 00:02:55.408
He said he couldn't predict.

55
00:02:55.512 --> 00:02:57.820
No. he said that the trial
was your best shot.

56
00:02:57.914 --> 00:02:59.032
You don't want to do it. fine.

57
00:02:59.116 --> 00:03:00.830
Then do it for me.
I can live with that.

58
00:03:00.895 --> 00:03:01.776
Just want to think about it.

59
00:03:01.825 --> 00:03:03.411
There's nothing to think about.

60
00:03:05.463 --> 00:03:06.939
I don't care if you get fat.

61
00:03:07.044 --> 00:03:08.964
I don't care
if you lose your hair.

62
00:03:09.054 --> 00:03:11.114
You're applying for this trial.

63
00:03:11.190 --> 00:03:13.877
You're gonna be accepted.
Do you understand me?

64
00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:16.288
I am not losing you.

65
00:03:18.587 --> 00:03:20.507
Soon as I get to the office...

66
00:03:21.141 --> 00:03:22.332
I'll make the call.

67
00:03:34.774 --> 00:03:37.267
Liz: DMV? Really?

68
00:03:37.859 --> 00:03:39.886
I've never even seen you drive.

69
00:03:40.119 --> 00:03:41.027
That little fella.

70
00:03:41.137 --> 00:03:44.352
the one through the glass.
his name is Glen Carter.

71
00:03:44.565 --> 00:03:46.743
His mother calls him
"Jelly Bean."

72
00:03:47.466 --> 00:03:50.009
A loathsome individual
who. sad to say.

73
00:03:50.085 --> 00:03:52.961
possesses an uncanny ability
to locate anything.

74
00:03:53.047 --> 00:03:55.656
Achoo!
[ Coughs ]

75
00:04:00.891 --> 00:04:02.287
[ Sighs ]

76
00:04:02.361 --> 00:04:05.129
I presume you've heard
of Justin Kenyon?

77
00:04:05.278 --> 00:04:07.899
The smiling public face
of the militia movement.

78
00:04:07.977 --> 00:04:08.935
Who hasn't?

79
00:04:09.019 --> 00:04:11.710
Yes.
The very voice of reason.

80
00:04:11.839 --> 00:04:14.329
the rebel darling
of the fringe right--

81
00:04:14.401 --> 00:04:16.638
charming. rustic.
camera-ready.

82
00:04:16.723 --> 00:04:20.591
the perfect spokesman to spin
vile hatred and prejudice

83
00:04:20.682 --> 00:04:24.329
into treacly dross that passes
for plainspoken common sense.

84
00:04:24.400 --> 00:04:25.662
Forget it.

85
00:04:26.465 --> 00:04:27.401
Excuse me?

86
00:04:27.455 --> 00:04:29.483
Justice knows exactly
who Justin Kenyon is.

87
00:04:29.544 --> 00:04:30.992
We know what he is.

88
00:04:31.054 --> 00:04:33.469
The Church of the Shield
is a cesspool

89
00:04:33.576 --> 00:04:35.661
of polygamy. doomsday paranoia.

90
00:04:35.762 --> 00:04:38.005
ritualized elder
and child abuse.

91
00:04:38.107 --> 00:04:41.174
but he also has four of the most
prominent civil rights attorneys

92
00:04:41.266 --> 00:04:43.778
in the country on retainer--
we can't touch him.

93
00:04:43.846 --> 00:04:44.988
How do you suppose he pays

94
00:04:45.067 --> 00:04:46.492
for those
high-priced lawyers--

95
00:04:46.563 --> 00:04:47.484
charitable contributions?

96
00:04:47.544 --> 00:04:48.685
His church has been audited

97
00:04:48.747 --> 00:04:51.254
by the IRS every year
for the past decade.

98
00:04:51.371 --> 00:04:53.782
His books are impeccable.

99
00:04:54.898 --> 00:04:56.282
So are mine.

100
00:04:57.787 --> 00:05:00.672
Liz: Justin Kenyon-- head of
the Church of the Shield.

101
00:05:00.804 --> 00:05:05.712
a polygamist cult located
on a 15.000-acre reserve

102
00:05:05.941 --> 00:05:07.424
in the Smoky Mountains.

103
00:05:07.520 --> 00:05:08.967
Aram: Kenyon declared it
a nation-state

104
00:05:09.045 --> 00:05:10.035
and petitioned to secede

105
00:05:10.112 --> 00:05:11.928
in US District Court
three decades ago.

106
00:05:12.067 --> 00:05:12.955
According to Reddington.

107
00:05:13.045 --> 00:05:14.796
Kenyon has dozens
of shipping containers

108
00:05:14.878 --> 00:05:16.111
buried on his property.

109
00:05:16.198 --> 00:05:17.302
Terrorists. cartels.

110
00:05:17.382 --> 00:05:19.561
and criminals contract with him
to store cargo.

111
00:05:19.673 --> 00:05:21.202
no questions asked.

112
00:05:21.333 --> 00:05:23.153
Reddington compiled
a partial inventory

113
00:05:23.221 --> 00:05:24.255
from his sources.

114
00:05:24.333 --> 00:05:26.121
It includes all manner
of contraband.

115
00:05:26.211 --> 00:05:29.291
from drugs and hot merchandise
to military ordnance.

116
00:05:29.364 --> 00:05:32.909
antiaircraft guns.
missiles. RPGs. Semtex.

117
00:05:33.022 --> 00:05:34.427
Sounds like a one-stop
storage facility

118
00:05:34.504 --> 00:05:35.642
for the criminal underworld.

119
00:05:35.703 --> 00:05:36.670
In 1982.

120
00:05:36.761 --> 00:05:40.157
Kenyon published a book entitled
"The Silver Bear Prophecies."

121
00:05:40.263 --> 00:05:41.864
which he purported
were delivered to him

122
00:05:41.942 --> 00:05:44.802
by the spirit of
an ancient Druid elder.

123
00:05:44.899 --> 00:05:47.405
In it. he claims to be
the latter-day incarnation

124
00:05:47.515 --> 00:05:51.156
of an entity the Silver Bear
called "The Ken'yon."

125
00:05:51.237 --> 00:05:52.070
How convenient.

126
00:05:52.153 --> 00:05:56.569
Ken'yon and his followers will
ascend into Heaven for six days

127
00:05:56.668 --> 00:05:58.820
and return to--
and I quote--

128
00:05:58.925 --> 00:06:01.380
"Rain fire
upon the New Babylon.

129
00:06:01.532 --> 00:06:03.647
the defiled States of America.

130
00:06:03.728 --> 00:06:06.191
and our children shall cleanse
her streets

131
00:06:06.280 --> 00:06:08.676
with the blood
of her founder's enemies."

132
00:06:08.752 --> 00:06:09.636
According to Reddington.

133
00:06:09.760 --> 00:06:11.621
Ken'yon has fallen off
the radar.

134
00:06:12.080 --> 00:06:13.939
His clients have been unable
to reach him

135
00:06:14.009 --> 00:06:16.349
or anyone on the compound
since last Saturday.

136
00:06:16.425 --> 00:06:19.254
Which means they don't have
access to their stored goods.

137
00:06:19.354 --> 00:06:20.583
As you can imagine.

138
00:06:20.680 --> 00:06:22.730
this makes a number
of very dangerous people

139
00:06:22.811 --> 00:06:24.664
very. very nervous.

140
00:06:24.787 --> 00:06:28.609
[ Laughs ] Not interested.
Can't be done.

141
00:06:28.699 --> 00:06:32.098
Glen. you have found things
for me with far less to go on.

142
00:06:32.184 --> 00:06:33.634
Ernie's retirement party's
tonight.

143
00:06:33.698 --> 00:06:34.967
I got to pick up
the shrimp platter.

144
00:06:35.043 --> 00:06:36.476
You found Jerry Minkie's wife

145
00:06:36.571 --> 00:06:38.333
after she ran off
with the uber driver.

146
00:06:38.405 --> 00:06:39.424
the one with the Subaru.

147
00:06:39.496 --> 00:06:40.410
I don't even like shrimp.

148
00:06:40.479 --> 00:06:43.248
You found. uh. the other guy--
who was that?-- That...

149
00:06:43.367 --> 00:06:46.183
mobster who was hiding out
in needles.

150
00:06:46.333 --> 00:06:48.371
Glen. look. you and I...

151
00:06:49.213 --> 00:06:50.645
we've had our differences.

152
00:06:50.739 --> 00:06:53.249
but I have enormous respect
for your abilities.

153
00:06:53.324 --> 00:06:54.067
You<i> know</i> that.

154
00:06:54.143 --> 00:06:56.033
If anyone can help me.
it's you.

155
00:06:56.099 --> 00:06:58.987
It's not the shrimp.
It's the dip. that sauce.

156
00:06:59.093 --> 00:07:00.657
I don't like sauces.

157
00:07:01.721 --> 00:07:02.530
[ Paper rustles ]

158
00:07:02.616 --> 00:07:03.988
You know what?
Forget it. I don't need this.

159
00:07:04.050 --> 00:07:05.078
What are you so upset about?

160
00:07:05.137 --> 00:07:07.313
There isn't a retirement party.
is there?!

161
00:07:07.430 --> 00:07:08.403
You're making it up!

162
00:07:08.484 --> 00:07:09.892
<i>That's</i> what this is about!

163
00:07:09.973 --> 00:07:10.957
This is what you want--

164
00:07:11.036 --> 00:07:13.235
to see me get all lathered up!

165
00:07:13.334 --> 00:07:15.484
You're pathological.
You realize that. right?

166
00:07:15.646 --> 00:07:18.550
Ernie's shrimp platter?!
You can't be serious!

167
00:07:18.631 --> 00:07:21.061
Do you even see the irony
in that?

168
00:07:21.129 --> 00:07:22.373
[ Groans ]

169
00:07:23.716 --> 00:07:24.681
[ Sighs ]

170
00:07:25.511 --> 00:07:27.090
Tell me about the safe.

171
00:07:27.872 --> 00:07:29.305
Glen. I'm upset!

172
00:07:29.372 --> 00:07:32.315
Your spook friend--
he said it was critical.

173
00:07:39.775 --> 00:07:40.653
[ Sighs ]

174
00:07:42.235 --> 00:07:43.533
As I've already told you.

175
00:07:43.613 --> 00:07:46.175
he said there is a safe
in St. Petersburg

176
00:07:46.298 --> 00:07:48.705
on the second floor of
I don't know where--

177
00:07:48.793 --> 00:07:50.569
a bank. an apartment.

178
00:07:50.636 --> 00:07:52.630
He died before
he could tell me more.

179
00:07:52.703 --> 00:07:54.255
The spook...

180
00:07:54.669 --> 00:07:56.056
What was his name?

181
00:07:56.668 --> 00:07:58.757
Alan Fitch.

182
00:07:59.034 --> 00:08:00.289
Alan...

183
00:08:02.313 --> 00:08:03.442
Fitch!

184
00:08:04.298 --> 00:08:05.352
Fitch.

185
00:08:07.532 --> 00:08:09.466
Kenyon's been off the grid
for three days.

186
00:08:09.929 --> 00:08:11.894
According to his own words.
that gives us 72 hours

187
00:08:11.970 --> 00:08:14.269
before he delivers his version
of armageddon.

188
00:08:14.341 --> 00:08:16.675
His counsel has assured us
nothing is amiss.

189
00:08:16.763 --> 00:08:18.029
and under no circumstances

190
00:08:18.131 --> 00:08:20.373
are we to attempt
direct contact.

191
00:08:20.457 --> 00:08:21.925
They've already won
two civil judgments

192
00:08:22.003 --> 00:08:23.656
on Kenyon's behalf
for harassment.

193
00:08:23.728 --> 00:08:25.385
That was before we knew he was
sitting on enough ordnance

194
00:08:25.470 --> 00:08:26.701
to arm
a third-world country.

195
00:08:26.766 --> 00:08:29.562
This could all go south fast
and end up looking very badly.

196
00:08:29.619 --> 00:08:30.686
I don't give a damn
how it looks.

197
00:08:30.746 --> 00:08:32.314
Well. that's a luxury
we cannot afford.

198
00:08:32.543 --> 00:08:34.587
not after Waco and Ruby Ridge.

199
00:08:34.670 --> 00:08:36.769
We're looking
at a tactical nightmare--

200
00:08:36.865 --> 00:08:39.355
78 square miles
of virgin forest.

201
00:08:39.505 --> 00:08:40.524
a mountain stronghold

202
00:08:40.593 --> 00:08:42.029
with enough food
and potable water

203
00:08:42.115 --> 00:08:44.742
to withstand an armed siege
for months.

204
00:08:44.817 --> 00:08:46.108
And even if by some miracle

205
00:08:46.266 --> 00:08:47.961
we manage
to put down resistance

206
00:08:48.047 --> 00:08:50.024
and seize that compound
without loss of life.

207
00:08:50.108 --> 00:08:53.664
without harm coming to the
26 children who reside there.

208
00:08:54.027 --> 00:08:55.597
what if Reddington is wrong?

209
00:08:55.683 --> 00:08:57.560
Lizzy. exactly when
have I been wrong?

210
00:08:57.645 --> 00:09:00.105
I told you-- there are
political considerations.

211
00:09:00.196 --> 00:09:02.673
If we raid Kenyon's compound
and come up empty-handed--

212
00:09:02.744 --> 00:09:04.348
You will<i> not</i> come up
empty-handed.

213
00:09:04.435 --> 00:09:05.587
But if we do.

214
00:09:05.700 --> 00:09:07.600
then we'll have validated
Kenyon's allegations

215
00:09:07.702 --> 00:09:10.378
that the federal government
are a pack of jackbooted thugs.

216
00:09:10.510 --> 00:09:13.006
We'll have raised him up as
a martyr for the constitution.

217
00:09:13.078 --> 00:09:14.717
That's exactly what he wants.

218
00:09:14.794 --> 00:09:16.824
Lizzy. I have gone
to considerable lengths

219
00:09:16.906 --> 00:09:19.370
to point you and your team
in the right direction.

220
00:09:19.472 --> 00:09:22.221
and now. due to
political considerations.

221
00:09:22.327 --> 00:09:24.676
people will die.

222
00:09:24.757 --> 00:09:25.903
And when they do

223
00:09:25.979 --> 00:09:28.856
and the bureaucrats decide
that the loss of innocent lives

224
00:09:28.965 --> 00:09:30.472
trumps their career prospects.

225
00:09:30.591 --> 00:09:32.335
you be sure to give me a call.

226
00:09:35.180 --> 00:09:38.407
_

227
00:09:41.478 --> 00:09:43.300
Unit B61 to Dispatch.

228
00:09:43.396 --> 00:09:45.311
run a check
on a late-model Chevy van.

229
00:09:45.439 --> 00:09:49.672
Tennessee plate number
Delta-Oscar-Charlie-7-7-1.

230
00:09:51.990 --> 00:09:55.194
Woman: Unit B261. that tag
number is 10-40 stolen.

231
00:09:55.332 --> 00:09:58.493
registered to
a 2005 Jeep Cherokee.

232
00:09:58.564 --> 00:09:59.916
- Copy?
- Copy that.

233
00:10:01.392 --> 00:10:03.038
[ Gun cocks ]

234
00:10:03.229 --> 00:10:04.496
Show us your hands!

235
00:10:07.907 --> 00:10:10.479
Hands outside the window now!

236
00:10:14.497 --> 00:10:15.459
What the...

237
00:10:16.218 --> 00:10:17.366
Hold your fire!

238
00:10:18.499 --> 00:10:19.643
It's just a--

239
00:10:26.136 --> 00:10:28.647
ATF estimates there was enough
Semtex in that van

240
00:10:28.746 --> 00:10:30.343
to level five square blocks.

241
00:10:30.412 --> 00:10:31.971
- Anything on the victims?
- Vaporized.

242
00:10:32.073 --> 00:10:34.399
The presumed dead include
two Alabama State troopers

243
00:10:34.498 --> 00:10:35.461
and the occupant of the van.

244
00:10:35.575 --> 00:10:36.899
- [ Cellphone rings ]
- Yeah?

245
00:10:38.581 --> 00:10:40.573
We just got footage
of the explosion.

246
00:10:41.116 --> 00:10:42.786
<i>Hold your fire!</i>
<i>It's just a--</i>

247
00:10:44.440 --> 00:10:45.677
It's just a<i> what?</i>

248
00:10:45.767 --> 00:10:46.892
Aram: The VIN numbers
on the van's differential

249
00:10:46.995 --> 00:10:49.796
match a vehicle registered to
Kenyon's Church of the Shield.

250
00:10:49.960 --> 00:10:52.162
Judge is signing
the search warrant as we speak.

251
00:10:52.400 --> 00:10:53.760
Also. the plates
were swapped out

252
00:10:53.854 --> 00:10:55.018
for one stolen off a Cherokee

253
00:10:55.097 --> 00:10:56.946
at a truck stop
five miles down the road

254
00:10:57.052 --> 00:10:58.258
from the Kenyon compound.

255
00:10:58.312 --> 00:10:59.620
I got a hit
on another set of plates

256
00:10:59.722 --> 00:11:01.852
stolen from the same location.

257
00:11:01.951 --> 00:11:03.342
Another van passed through
a tollbooth

258
00:11:03.421 --> 00:11:05.873
on the MD 200 headed into DC.

259
00:11:05.960 --> 00:11:06.929
Ressler:
Reddington was right.

260
00:11:07.019 --> 00:11:07.698
If we'd listened to him.

261
00:11:07.787 --> 00:11:08.929
we wouldn't have a gang
of fanatics

262
00:11:09.013 --> 00:11:11.470
joyriding with enough ordnance
to level a small city.

263
00:11:11.547 --> 00:11:12.950
Ressler and Keen.
get to that compound.

264
00:11:13.022 --> 00:11:14.217
The warrant should be sealed
and delivered

265
00:11:14.272 --> 00:11:15.196
by the time you arrive.

266
00:11:15.277 --> 00:11:17.249
Navabi. the van--
find out everything you can.

267
00:11:17.409 --> 00:11:20.147
[ Cellphone rings ]

268
00:11:21.101 --> 00:11:22.193
Harold Cooper.

269
00:11:23.692 --> 00:11:25.723
Dr. Levin. hello.

270
00:11:28.197 --> 00:11:29.704
W-was I accepted?

271
00:11:33.969 --> 00:11:35.342
I see.

272
00:11:36.394 --> 00:11:39.491
You know. Jeff.
you don't owe me an apology.

273
00:11:39.557 --> 00:11:41.613
I know you did everything
you could.

274
00:11:42.796 --> 00:11:44.446
Thank you.

275
00:11:50.902 --> 00:11:53.372
[ Beeps. dialing ]

276
00:11:55.739 --> 00:11:57.983
Hey. I just got off the phone
with the doctor.

277
00:11:58.994 --> 00:12:00.899
I'm afraid it's... bad news.

278
00:12:01.823 --> 00:12:04.602
I am<i> not</i> taking you
to St. Petersburg.

279
00:12:04.687 --> 00:12:06.264
You are if you want to know
where the safe is.

280
00:12:06.336 --> 00:12:09.024
- How do I even know you've found it?
- You don't.

281
00:12:09.103 --> 00:12:10.882
But I got two weeks of vacation
I got to take

282
00:12:11.021 --> 00:12:12.884
before the end of the year
or I lose it.

283
00:12:12.996 --> 00:12:13.838
It's February!

284
00:12:13.948 --> 00:12:14.964
We could take your jet.

285
00:12:15.216 --> 00:12:16.697
have a few laughs on the way.

286
00:12:16.765 --> 00:12:18.994
some of those nuts--
the honey-roasted ones.

287
00:12:19.093 --> 00:12:22.288
I want what I paid for--

288
00:12:22.416 --> 00:12:25.130
the location of the safe.

289
00:12:25.201 --> 00:12:26.796
Can I be honest with you?

290
00:12:26.871 --> 00:12:28.242
I doubt it.

291
00:12:29.491 --> 00:12:31.759
I've never been out
of the country.

292
00:12:33.169 --> 00:12:35.492
My dad. our vacations as a kid.

293
00:12:35.590 --> 00:12:36.975
we drove everywhere--

294
00:12:37.065 --> 00:12:39.650
South Dakota. Florida.

295
00:12:39.740 --> 00:12:41.861
But you-- I look at you...

296
00:12:43.167 --> 00:12:45.902
and all the places you go...

297
00:12:48.509 --> 00:12:53.239
and I'd just like
to do that once.

298
00:12:54.697 --> 00:12:56.913
Plus. I think it'd be fun.

299
00:12:57.617 --> 00:13:00.320
I feel like
we might have a good time.

300
00:13:04.268 --> 00:13:05.415
[ Sighs ]

301
00:13:11.999 --> 00:13:13.158
[ Scoffs ]

302
00:13:14.178 --> 00:13:15.382
I'm screwing with you!

303
00:13:15.476 --> 00:13:16.524
I was born in London.

304
00:13:16.620 --> 00:13:18.097
but I've never been
on a private jet.

305
00:13:18.248 --> 00:13:20.302
[ Clears throat ]
Anyway. I clock out at 5:30.

306
00:13:20.408 --> 00:13:21.867
I'll need to stop by the house.

307
00:13:21.950 --> 00:13:22.985
grab a shower.

308
00:13:23.082 --> 00:13:24.224
feed the turtle.

309
00:13:24.520 --> 00:13:27.305
I can have a bag packed
and be wheels up by 9:00.

310
00:13:27.402 --> 00:13:28.496
[ Sighs ]

311
00:13:29.665 --> 00:13:31.567
_

312
00:13:31.788 --> 00:13:33.062
Sheriff. have you met Kenyon?

313
00:13:33.191 --> 00:13:36.137
He makes a habit of coming
into town for breakfast.

314
00:13:36.242 --> 00:13:37.295
He's a bit of a blowhard

315
00:13:37.397 --> 00:13:39.575
but always friendly.
cooperative.

316
00:13:39.947 --> 00:13:43.029
Plus. the church has provided
volunteers for community events.

317
00:13:43.133 --> 00:13:44.784
search-and-rescue operations.

318
00:13:45.044 --> 00:13:45.872
So. what are you
suggesting--

319
00:13:45.966 --> 00:13:49.326
we collar this guy at the next
rotary club pancake breakfast?

320
00:13:49.417 --> 00:13:51.546
I'm suggesting
he can be talked to.

321
00:13:51.667 --> 00:13:52.741
He's reasonable.

322
00:13:52.825 --> 00:13:55.261
and I'm suggesting you let
my boys handle this

323
00:13:55.382 --> 00:13:57.032
instead of lighting
this whole mountain up

324
00:13:57.113 --> 00:13:58.902
and starting World War III.

325
00:13:58.981 --> 00:14:01.202
What are the odds we'll be met
with armed resistance?

326
00:14:01.341 --> 00:14:02.595
It's a dead certainty.

327
00:14:02.733 --> 00:14:04.823
You step one foot
on Kenyon's land

328
00:14:04.864 --> 00:14:07.615
without his express consent.
he'll put a bullet in you.

329
00:14:07.800 --> 00:14:09.539
badge or no badge.

330
00:14:17.094 --> 00:14:18.816
_

331
00:14:18.988 --> 00:14:20.321
Now. we've cleared
the estimated kill zone.

332
00:14:20.414 --> 00:14:22.012
and we've evacuated
the surrounding areas.

333
00:14:22.142 --> 00:14:23.714
We're waiting
on a sniper team now.

334
00:14:25.132 --> 00:14:26.173
Navabi:
Hold your fire.

335
00:14:26.298 --> 00:14:27.456
It's just...

336
00:14:28.465 --> 00:14:30.038
a kid.

337
00:14:30.608 --> 00:14:32.220
It's just a kid.

338
00:14:35.857 --> 00:14:37.815
- Excuse me. miss?
- Take this.

339
00:14:37.930 --> 00:14:38.805
Hey. h-hold on!

340
00:14:38.880 --> 00:14:40.647
Hey. halt! No!

341
00:14:41.478 --> 00:14:43.670
Return to the firing line!

342
00:14:43.734 --> 00:14:45.804
Do not approach the suspect!

343
00:14:45.959 --> 00:14:49.358
Return to the firing line!
Do not approach the suspect!

344
00:14:56.159 --> 00:14:57.732
Hi.

345
00:14:59.766 --> 00:15:03.498
I'm Samar.
What's your name?

346
00:15:06.783 --> 00:15:08.792
Do you know what that does?

347
00:15:10.614 --> 00:15:13.593
You planned on killing a lot
of people today.

348
00:15:14.466 --> 00:15:16.162
Was that your mission?

349
00:15:18.608 --> 00:15:21.828
It's not going to happen.
Do you see?

350
00:15:23.659 --> 00:15:26.012
They're all too far away.

351
00:15:26.387 --> 00:15:27.873
There's no point now.

352
00:15:27.981 --> 00:15:30.177
It's just the two of us
out here.

353
00:15:30.705 --> 00:15:32.704
If you push that button...

354
00:15:33.924 --> 00:15:36.407
only two of us
are going to die.

355
00:15:36.479 --> 00:15:37.914
Do you understand?

356
00:15:37.997 --> 00:15:39.781
Just you and me.

357
00:15:39.850 --> 00:15:41.913
and I don't want to die today.

358
00:15:44.711 --> 00:15:46.422
Do you?

359
00:15:57.335 --> 00:15:58.641
Come on out.

360
00:15:58.945 --> 00:15:59.997
Come on.

361
00:16:00.866 --> 00:16:03.174
[ Breathing heavily ]

362
00:16:03.242 --> 00:16:04.662
Come here. give me your hand.

363
00:16:04.810 --> 00:16:05.591
It's gonna be okay.

364
00:16:05.662 --> 00:16:07.418
♪ show me the way ♪

365
00:16:07.536 --> 00:16:11.423
♪ oh. brothers. let's go down ♪

366
00:16:11.547 --> 00:16:15.633
♪ let's go down. come on down ♪

367
00:16:15.804 --> 00:16:20.545
♪ down in the river to pray ♪

368
00:16:20.689 --> 00:16:24.931
♪ as I went down in the river
to pray ♪

369
00:16:25.044 --> 00:16:29.032
♪ studying about
that good old way ♪

370
00:16:29.084 --> 00:16:33.235
♪ and who shall wear the robe
and crown? ♪

371
00:16:33.332 --> 00:16:37.708
♪ good lord. show me the way ♪

372
00:16:38.113 --> 00:16:40.762
♪ oh. brothers. let's go down ♪

373
00:16:40.815 --> 00:16:41.914
Go. go!

374
00:16:42.382 --> 00:16:46.409
♪ let's go down. come on down ♪

375
00:16:46.534 --> 00:16:50.549
♪ come on. brothers.
let's go down ♪

376
00:16:50.654 --> 00:16:55.340
♪ down in the river to pray ♪

377
00:16:55.412 --> 00:16:59.121
♪ oh. mothers. let's go down ♪

378
00:16:59.233 --> 00:17:03.349
♪ come on down.
don't you want to go down? ♪

379
00:17:03.452 --> 00:17:07.459
♪ come on. mothers.
let's go down ♪

380
00:17:07.555 --> 00:17:11.879
♪ down in the river to pray ♪

381
00:17:13.807 --> 00:17:18.505
_

382
00:17:18.985 --> 00:17:20.357
Liz:
Kenyon's unaccounted for.

383
00:17:20.485 --> 00:17:23.052
53 of his followers
slaughtered.

384
00:17:23.256 --> 00:17:24.618
No sign of him.

385
00:17:24.736 --> 00:17:25.847
Red: That's puzzling.

386
00:17:25.917 --> 00:17:27.521
It appears all the adults
were murdered

387
00:17:27.627 --> 00:17:29.480
and the children are gone.

388
00:17:29.567 --> 00:17:31.523
Kenyon's ideology
has always been

389
00:17:31.601 --> 00:17:34.825
about vanquishing the infidels
and rising to power.

390
00:17:34.902 --> 00:17:36.386
not about killing their own.

391
00:17:36.461 --> 00:17:37.846
This is a group
of survivalists.

392
00:17:37.932 --> 00:17:40.077
They might have been attacked
by a rival militia.

393
00:17:40.164 --> 00:17:42.886
We found a number of dead bodies
surrounding the perimeter.

394
00:17:42.957 --> 00:17:44.029
And the storage containers?

395
00:17:44.104 --> 00:17:46.056
Located. secured.
and searched--

396
00:17:46.216 --> 00:17:48.116
about a dozen of them so far.

397
00:17:48.187 --> 00:17:49.731
They've been pretty much
cleaned out--

398
00:17:49.826 --> 00:17:51.947
no weapons. no ordnance.

399
00:17:52.053 --> 00:17:53.616
According to an inventory list.

400
00:17:53.708 --> 00:17:57.776
we're missing small arms. RPGs.
three Hellfire missiles.

401
00:17:57.870 --> 00:18:00.000
plus over a ton of Semtex.

402
00:18:00.095 --> 00:18:02.772
C4. Demex. and plastite.

403
00:18:03.898 --> 00:18:05.178
What was that?

404
00:18:05.298 --> 00:18:07.798
That was... a vase.

405
00:18:07.927 --> 00:18:09.118
What about the vehicles?

406
00:18:09.191 --> 00:18:10.905
All the church's vehicles
are accounted for.

407
00:18:10.979 --> 00:18:12.664
except for one.

408
00:18:13.676 --> 00:18:14.944
Another bomb.

409
00:18:15.028 --> 00:18:16.350
Something's gone sideways.
Lizzy.

410
00:18:16.446 --> 00:18:17.329
[ Object rattles ]

411
00:18:17.429 --> 00:18:18.929
Kenyon is the devil we know.

412
00:18:19.023 --> 00:18:21.217
but now either
others are involved

413
00:18:21.305 --> 00:18:24.235
or there's been a complete
breakdown in the organization.

414
00:18:24.309 --> 00:18:26.790
Either way.
be careful out there.

415
00:18:27.394 --> 00:18:29.132
[ Toilet flushes ]

416
00:18:30.055 --> 00:18:31.592
You're<i> sure</i> this is
the apartment?

417
00:18:31.671 --> 00:18:33.501
- This is the apartment.
- You're positive?

418
00:18:33.601 --> 00:18:34.768
Your tone is insulting.

419
00:18:34.850 --> 00:18:36.340
My tone?!

420
00:18:36.562 --> 00:18:39.839
I endured 13 hours with you
on my jet.

421
00:18:39.980 --> 00:18:41.988
12 of which
you had your shoes off.

422
00:18:42.100 --> 00:18:43.024
You snored.

423
00:18:43.118 --> 00:18:44.713
You insulted
my flight attendant!

424
00:18:44.787 --> 00:18:46.109
I thought she was pregnant.

425
00:18:46.189 --> 00:18:47.740
Glen. the safe!

426
00:18:47.812 --> 00:18:48.946
We haven't found it yet.
have we?!

427
00:18:49.028 --> 00:18:51.912
I know everything one can
possibly know about Alan Fitch.

428
00:18:51.992 --> 00:18:53.658
I worked on this
'round the clock.

429
00:18:53.788 --> 00:18:57.214
and you know how irritable I can
be if I don't get my 10 hours.

430
00:18:57.329 --> 00:18:59.804
I've reviewed six years
of bank records.

431
00:18:59.885 --> 00:19:01.557
and I traced the cash payment
he made

432
00:19:01.657 --> 00:19:05.070
to purchase an apartment
in this very building

433
00:19:05.176 --> 00:19:07.363
on this very floor.

434
00:19:08.304 --> 00:19:10.773
Trust me. the safe is here.

435
00:19:10.844 --> 00:19:12.549
I don't trust you.

436
00:19:21.076 --> 00:19:22.218
What the hell is this?

437
00:19:22.310 --> 00:19:24.761
The title to apartment 221.

438
00:19:25.281 --> 00:19:27.343
Apology accepted.

439
00:19:28.462 --> 00:19:29.917
What?

440
00:19:30.124 --> 00:19:32.643
We're in apartment 212.

441
00:19:35.002 --> 00:19:36.470
You don't know the cross
that I bear.

442
00:19:36.567 --> 00:19:38.699
the things I've had
to overcome--

443
00:19:38.825 --> 00:19:39.951
my dyslexia.

444
00:19:40.046 --> 00:19:41.784
- You're not dyslexic.
Dembe: - Raymond.

445
00:19:41.885 --> 00:19:43.055
Oh. really. doctor?

446
00:19:43.139 --> 00:19:45.166
Is that your
professional opinion?

447
00:19:45.547 --> 00:19:47.332
Forgot to pack my medication.

448
00:19:47.419 --> 00:19:49.372
I was shocked when you told me
I could come along.

449
00:19:49.451 --> 00:19:50.316
It threw me.

450
00:19:50.416 --> 00:19:52.383
I left my dyslexia pills
on the counter.

451
00:19:52.471 --> 00:19:54.526
There are no pills
for dyslexia.

452
00:19:59.932 --> 00:20:02.334
Get this to Sorenson for a trace
on the number.

453
00:20:04.183 --> 00:20:04.999
Cooper: How old is he?

454
00:20:05.085 --> 00:20:06.817
Navabi: - He's 10.
- 10?

455
00:20:07.024 --> 00:20:08.030
What the hell are we
dealing with here?

456
00:20:08.111 --> 00:20:10.016
I've seen this before
in fanatical sects.

457
00:20:10.103 --> 00:20:12.111
The children are indoctrinated
from the time they're born.

458
00:20:12.231 --> 00:20:13.948
force-fed by rod and rote--

459
00:20:14.048 --> 00:20:17.426
In this case. the gospel
according to Justin Kenyon.

460
00:20:17.504 --> 00:20:19.537
To rain fire
upon the New Babylon.

461
00:20:19.622 --> 00:20:21.140
Aram: Oh. my God--
coroner's preliminary report

462
00:20:21.218 --> 00:20:22.698
on the massacre
at the compound.

463
00:20:22.776 --> 00:20:24.668
- What do you got?
- Not a shot was fired.

464
00:20:24.778 --> 00:20:26.547
Every single one of those people
was stabbed.

465
00:20:26.651 --> 00:20:29.422
strangled. stomped.
or bludgeoned to death.

466
00:20:29.523 --> 00:20:31.103
- Dear God.
- And something else.

467
00:20:31.206 --> 00:20:32.955
A field office in Richmond
just got a call

468
00:20:33.046 --> 00:20:35.040
from a former cult member--

469
00:20:35.457 --> 00:20:37.005
Dawn Weston.

470
00:20:37.096 --> 00:20:39.907
Swears our truck bomber
is her son.

471
00:20:40.374 --> 00:20:42.458
Liz: She's our only
surviving witness.

472
00:20:42.552 --> 00:20:44.564
Starkweather: Of a crime
committed in my jurisdiction.

473
00:20:44.683 --> 00:20:46.442
That makes her
my responsibility.

474
00:20:46.526 --> 00:20:47.892
Ressler: Look. these are
dangerous people.

475
00:20:47.976 --> 00:20:48.835
We have an entire unit

476
00:20:48.917 --> 00:20:50.451
tasked with providing
protective custody.

477
00:20:50.533 --> 00:20:52.338
There's no point in
hashing this out now.

478
00:20:52.418 --> 00:20:53.738
No matter how this shakes down.

479
00:20:53.859 --> 00:20:54.946
the first thing we need to do

480
00:20:55.043 --> 00:20:58.304
is get that girl safely off
this mountain-- agreed?

481
00:21:02.777 --> 00:21:03.987
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

482
00:21:10.563 --> 00:21:12.256
What are you looking at?

483
00:21:12.709 --> 00:21:14.167
Watchers.

484
00:21:14.558 --> 00:21:15.711
Watchers?

485
00:21:15.935 --> 00:21:18.208
Shh. it's a secret.

486
00:21:30.130 --> 00:21:32.106
I thought he was dead.

487
00:21:32.297 --> 00:21:33.575
Your son. Finnian.

488
00:21:33.670 --> 00:21:36.078
Finn. we always called him.

489
00:21:36.673 --> 00:21:39.323
[ Sobs ]
Finn.

490
00:21:39.826 --> 00:21:42.128
[ Sobbing ]

491
00:21:44.273 --> 00:21:46.656
There are some things
that you need to understand

492
00:21:46.752 --> 00:21:50.111
about Justin. about the way
that things were.

493
00:21:50.212 --> 00:21:53.031
You see. h-his word was not
just the law.

494
00:21:53.154 --> 00:21:56.195
It was the word of God himself.

495
00:21:56.368 --> 00:21:58.868
Justin was our oracle.

496
00:21:58.965 --> 00:22:00.852
He was our burning bush.

497
00:22:00.927 --> 00:22:01.765
I understand.

498
00:22:01.882 --> 00:22:02.672
You don't.

499
00:22:02.782 --> 00:22:06.033
You can't. not unless
you were there. You...

500
00:22:06.676 --> 00:22:08.238
God. what have I done?

501
00:22:08.768 --> 00:22:10.018
Tell me.

502
00:22:15.720 --> 00:22:17.572
According to Justin...

503
00:22:18.108 --> 00:22:22.229
each man was to take
unto himself three wives.

504
00:22:22.641 --> 00:22:24.704
Which wasn't a problem
in the early days.

505
00:22:24.782 --> 00:22:27.186
but as we began
to have children...

506
00:22:27.657 --> 00:22:29.664
he must've seen the flaw
in his plan.

507
00:22:29.750 --> 00:22:30.649
What flaw?

508
00:22:30.739 --> 00:22:33.485
There were too many boys.
of course.

509
00:22:33.598 --> 00:22:37.656
More than half the children
were. you know. male. and so...

510
00:22:38.535 --> 00:22:40.387
he began the walkabout.

511
00:22:40.496 --> 00:22:41.761
The walkabout?

512
00:22:41.854 --> 00:22:43.798
The first new moon in January.

513
00:22:43.872 --> 00:22:46.111
lots would be drawn
among the boys.

514
00:22:46.184 --> 00:22:48.713
We would have a great feast
in celebration.

515
00:22:48.816 --> 00:22:52.080
and the chosen one would be
the guest of honor.

516
00:22:52.159 --> 00:22:53.850
He was treated as a man.

517
00:22:53.920 --> 00:22:55.349
How old were the chosen?

518
00:22:55.428 --> 00:22:56.922
8 or 10.

519
00:22:57.846 --> 00:23:00.069
Just before the onset
of puberty.

520
00:23:00.134 --> 00:23:02.529
After the feast.
the boy would be awakened

521
00:23:02.638 --> 00:23:05.677
and taken deep into the woods.
and then...

522
00:23:05.825 --> 00:23:08.417
You left him there
in the middle of nowhere.

523
00:23:08.524 --> 00:23:10.123
in the bitter cold.

524
00:23:10.197 --> 00:23:12.531
He said there were too many.

525
00:23:12.595 --> 00:23:14.518
[ Gunshot. tires screeching ]

526
00:23:25.035 --> 00:23:25.549
You're hurt.

527
00:23:25.647 --> 00:23:26.836
[ Sighs ]
I'm okay.

528
00:23:26.917 --> 00:23:27.809
Ressler's pinned.

529
00:23:27.889 --> 00:23:29.928
Ressler. talk to me!
You injured?

530
00:23:30.067 --> 00:23:32.619
I don't think anything's broke.
but I'm stuck.

531
00:23:32.693 --> 00:23:34.843
I can't--
I can't budge this thing.

532
00:23:35.389 --> 00:23:36.469
[ Grunts ]

533
00:23:36.919 --> 00:23:38.119
The radio's shot.

534
00:23:40.513 --> 00:23:42.068
Anybody got cell reception?

535
00:23:42.218 --> 00:23:43.656
Mine's busted.

536
00:23:49.971 --> 00:23:51.082
[ Sighs ]

537
00:23:54.419 --> 00:23:55.761
Somebody live back there?

538
00:23:56.102 --> 00:23:57.617
Not that I know of.

539
00:23:57.882 --> 00:23:59.281
You wait by the car with Amy.

540
00:23:59.342 --> 00:24:00.693
I'm gonna see if I can go
get us some help.

541
00:24:00.775 --> 00:24:02.031
check out that smoke.

542
00:24:02.097 --> 00:24:03.364
Keep an eye on that girl.

543
00:24:11.236 --> 00:24:13.202
Shouldn't you be prepping
for your confirmation hearing?

544
00:24:13.274 --> 00:24:14.478
[ Laughs ]

545
00:24:14.609 --> 00:24:15.830
It's a no-brainer.

546
00:24:16.018 --> 00:24:17.639
You're looking at the next
Attorney General.

547
00:24:17.756 --> 00:24:18.887
I'm happy for you. Tom.

548
00:24:18.974 --> 00:24:21.026
For<i> us.</i> Harold. for us.

549
00:24:21.748 --> 00:24:24.481
I want you to consider taking
the Director's chair.

550
00:24:26.277 --> 00:24:28.486
Tom. I don't know.

551
00:24:28.613 --> 00:24:30.472
It's what we've always
talked about.

552
00:24:31.097 --> 00:24:33.363
A rising tide lifts all boats.

553
00:24:33.592 --> 00:24:34.990
I'm flattered. Tom.

554
00:24:37.165 --> 00:24:38.059
But I can't.

555
00:24:38.146 --> 00:24:40.212
I'm not leaving here
with a "No."

556
00:24:40.298 --> 00:24:41.454
I'd love to take you up
on this. Tom.

557
00:24:41.556 --> 00:24:42.910
You know I would.

558
00:24:43.846 --> 00:24:45.351
But I'm dealing with some...

559
00:24:45.881 --> 00:24:47.554
health issues.

560
00:24:48.964 --> 00:24:51.612
What. Harold?
Is it serious?

561
00:24:51.709 --> 00:24:55.337
To be honest with you. yeah.
It's very serious.

562
00:24:56.105 --> 00:24:58.470
There was a clinical trial
that held out some hope.

563
00:24:58.551 --> 00:24:59.902
but. uh...

564
00:25:07.105 --> 00:25:10.000
Look. you didn't come here
to talk about my health.

565
00:25:10.365 --> 00:25:13.690
I'm happy for you.
I really am.

566
00:25:30.953 --> 00:25:32.648
Amy:
Are you in the FBI?

567
00:25:33.059 --> 00:25:34.417
Yes. I am.

568
00:25:34.509 --> 00:25:37.694
My daddy says all the people
who work for the FBI

569
00:25:37.784 --> 00:25:39.129
are gonna go to Hell.

570
00:25:39.216 --> 00:25:41.221
Some days it feels like that.
sweetheart.

571
00:25:41.305 --> 00:25:43.834
He says they're gonna burn
in a lake of fire.

572
00:25:46.143 --> 00:25:47.516
Who's there?!

573
00:25:49.387 --> 00:25:50.224
[ Rustling ]

574
00:25:50.313 --> 00:25:51.231
What is it?

575
00:25:51.364 --> 00:25:52.553
Shh!

576
00:25:55.423 --> 00:25:56.903
Hey. Starkweather!

577
00:25:57.216 --> 00:25:58.221
Shh!

578
00:25:58.356 --> 00:26:00.234
- It's them.
- Who?

579
00:26:00.404 --> 00:26:01.927
The watchers.

580
00:26:09.175 --> 00:26:10.339
- [ Thudding ]
- Sweetie. come here.

581
00:26:12.544 --> 00:26:13.592
Get down. get down!

582
00:26:21.215 --> 00:26:23.846
♪ maybe I'll try and make it ♪

583
00:26:24.461 --> 00:26:26.984
♪ all about the weather ♪

584
00:26:27.571 --> 00:26:30.415
♪ maybe I'll try
and make it... ♪

585
00:26:33.172 --> 00:26:35.248
The only cure for corruption
is disruption.

586
00:26:35.342 --> 00:26:37.030
The only cure for corruption
is disruption.

587
00:26:37.165 --> 00:26:38.999
The only cure for corruption
is disruption.

588
00:26:39.122 --> 00:26:41.066
The only cure for corruption
is disruption.

589
00:26:41.187 --> 00:26:42.960
The only cure for corruption
is disruption.

590
00:26:43.123 --> 00:26:45.224
The only cure for corruption
is disruption.

591
00:26:45.331 --> 00:26:47.219
The only cure for corruption
is disruption.

592
00:26:47.322 --> 00:26:48.898
- The only cure--
- Finn.

593
00:26:50.591 --> 00:26:52.140
The father said
to his servants. "Quick.

594
00:26:52.257 --> 00:26:54.362
put a ring on his finger
and sandals on his feet."

595
00:26:54.445 --> 00:26:56.746
Do you r-remember me?

596
00:27:04.869 --> 00:27:07.211
- Mama?
- Yes. Finn.

597
00:27:08.474 --> 00:27:11.186
[ Crying ]

598
00:27:14.158 --> 00:27:15.922
You're telling me
that this attack

599
00:27:16.015 --> 00:27:17.977
was masterminded
by a bunch of kids?

600
00:27:18.096 --> 00:27:19.724
Not just kids-- a tribe.

601
00:27:19.859 --> 00:27:21.726
militarily instructed
by their elders

602
00:27:21.818 --> 00:27:22.923
from the time they could walk

603
00:27:23.015 --> 00:27:25.034
in tracking.
evasion techniques.

604
00:27:25.124 --> 00:27:27.257
hand-to-hand combat.
firearm training.

605
00:27:27.338 --> 00:27:28.426
And left to die in the woods?

606
00:27:28.515 --> 00:27:30.070
Starting with Kenyon's
own son. David.

607
00:27:30.165 --> 00:27:31.365
- Why?
- Come on. keep going.

608
00:27:31.445 --> 00:27:33.048
The gospel
according to Kenyon--

609
00:27:33.160 --> 00:27:35.871
"And each man shall have
unto himself three wives."

610
00:27:36.857 --> 00:27:38.155
There were too many boys.

611
00:27:38.297 --> 00:27:40.185
It was the only way
to maintain the ratio.

612
00:27:40.394 --> 00:27:42.813
The mountain was supposed to
kill the boys. but it didn't.

613
00:27:42.934 --> 00:27:44.866
It was a crucible.
The weak died--

614
00:27:44.956 --> 00:27:46.933
- injuries disease. exposure...
- Get out of here! Come on. get out!

615
00:27:47.033 --> 00:27:48.334
...but the strong
survived.

616
00:27:48.419 --> 00:27:50.325
perfectly adapted.
with their own laws.

617
00:27:50.428 --> 00:27:51.910
their own society.
their own gods.

618
00:27:52.002 --> 00:27:54.100
chief among which
was Justin Kenyon.

619
00:27:54.194 --> 00:27:56.454
- "Was"?
- David is their leader.

620
00:27:56.523 --> 00:27:58.935
A few weeks ago. he declared
his father an apostate.

621
00:27:59.016 --> 00:28:01.009
He said that Justin
had abandoned his calling

622
00:28:01.077 --> 00:28:02.147
and that it was up to them

623
00:28:02.224 --> 00:28:03.909
to fulfill the prophecies
of Ken'yon.

624
00:28:04.077 --> 00:28:06.375
Did he tell you where this
final truck bomb was headed?

625
00:28:06.549 --> 00:28:09.889
The only people who know
are the other drivers and David.

626
00:28:09.998 --> 00:28:11.861
I can't raise Liz or Ressler.

627
00:28:13.396 --> 00:28:17.053
Samar. my dear. bump in the road
I can help smooth over.

628
00:28:17.165 --> 00:28:18.801
or have the clouds
finally parted

629
00:28:18.886 --> 00:28:20.161
and this is a social call?

630
00:28:20.236 --> 00:28:21.380
She's missing.

631
00:28:21.452 --> 00:28:22.531
- Agent Keen?
- And Ressler.

632
00:28:22.631 --> 00:28:24.620
They were supposed to deliver
a witness two hours ago.

633
00:28:24.700 --> 00:28:26.826
They haven't been seen since
they left Kenyon's compound.

634
00:28:26.911 --> 00:28:27.923
Have you mounted a search?

635
00:28:28.025 --> 00:28:29.750
I'm on my way out
to assist HRT.

636
00:28:29.852 --> 00:28:31.489
but there are [Sighs] hundreds

637
00:28:31.586 --> 00:28:33.017
of square miles
of rugged terrain.

638
00:28:33.091 --> 00:28:34.266
It could take days.

639
00:28:34.341 --> 00:28:35.555
The weapons.

640
00:28:35.966 --> 00:28:38.947
Agent Keen said there was
a complete inventory list.

641
00:28:39.148 --> 00:28:40.100
You have it?

642
00:28:40.181 --> 00:28:41.609
Well. we have a manifest.
Why?

643
00:28:41.689 --> 00:28:43.059
Send it to me.

644
00:28:43.364 --> 00:28:46.879
♪ is that all there is? ♪

645
00:28:46.998 --> 00:28:48.421
♪ anyone ♪

646
00:28:48.657 --> 00:28:49.946
♪ anyone ♪

647
00:28:50.011 --> 00:28:52.662
♪ can you give me somebody? ♪

648
00:28:53.296 --> 00:28:54.964
♪ someone ♪

649
00:28:55.033 --> 00:28:56.329
♪ someone ♪

650
00:28:56.400 --> 00:28:59.508
- ♪ is that all there is? ♪
- Ressler?!

651
00:28:59.821 --> 00:29:01.167
♪ anyone ♪

652
00:29:01.317 --> 00:29:02.961
♪ anyone ♪

653
00:29:03.025 --> 00:29:05.624
♪ can you give me somebody... ♪

654
00:29:05.773 --> 00:29:07.995
[ Breathing heavily ]

655
00:29:14.277 --> 00:29:16.512
[ Engine revving in distance ]

656
00:29:17.700 --> 00:29:20.896
[ Revving continues ]

657
00:29:25.830 --> 00:29:27.735
[ Screaming ]

658
00:29:37.993 --> 00:29:39.719
Raymond!

659
00:29:39.818 --> 00:29:40.923
Ohh.

660
00:29:41.003 --> 00:29:42.350
Oh. that's a shame.

661
00:29:42.489 --> 00:29:43.711
Dendrobium?

662
00:29:43.774 --> 00:29:44.850
My own hybrid.

663
00:29:44.975 --> 00:29:47.061
I call them
"Snows of Everest."

664
00:29:47.151 --> 00:29:48.408
Lovely.

665
00:29:48.933 --> 00:29:50.058
Friend of yours?

666
00:29:50.153 --> 00:29:52.269
A small accounting problem.

667
00:29:52.642 --> 00:29:53.879
Ruth.

668
00:29:54.476 --> 00:29:55.561
Ruth!

669
00:29:56.726 --> 00:29:59.457
I'm afraid I'll need
your undivided attention.

670
00:30:01.459 --> 00:30:02.793
Put on his parka.

671
00:30:02.860 --> 00:30:05.054
Tie him from the back
of the snowmobile.

672
00:30:05.114 --> 00:30:06.746
I'll be out in a minute.

673
00:30:06.871 --> 00:30:08.665
Very well.

674
00:30:09.419 --> 00:30:11.158
You have my attention.

675
00:30:12.198 --> 00:30:13.485
Ruth...

676
00:30:13.578 --> 00:30:16.580
I will be forever
indebted to you

677
00:30:16.642 --> 00:30:18.613
if you could be so kind
as to provide me

678
00:30:18.726 --> 00:30:20.385
with the activation codes

679
00:30:20.466 --> 00:30:21.598
for the Hellfire missiles

680
00:30:21.704 --> 00:30:24.533
you have stored
at Justin Kenyon's compound.

681
00:30:26.373 --> 00:30:28.053
- [ Beep ]
- Yes.

682
00:30:30.183 --> 00:30:31.498
- Are you Navabi?
- Yeah.

683
00:30:31.594 --> 00:30:33.033
It's for you.

684
00:30:34.260 --> 00:30:35.022
This is Samar.

685
00:30:35.121 --> 00:30:37.734
Agent Navabi. what do you know
about Hellfire missiles?

686
00:30:37.822 --> 00:30:40.070
- What does that have to do with anything?
- Quite a lot. actually.

687
00:30:40.169 --> 00:30:42.043
There were three of them stolen
from the compound.

688
00:30:42.130 --> 00:30:44.276
I've since acquired
their activation codes.

689
00:30:44.376 --> 00:30:46.333
You're going to launch three
Hellfire missiles?

690
00:30:46.434 --> 00:30:48.010
[ Chuckles ]
Don't be silly.

691
00:30:48.224 --> 00:30:50.889
We just activated the cameras
in their nose cones.

692
00:30:50.996 --> 00:30:52.728
I've seen quite a lot
of activity.

693
00:30:52.824 --> 00:30:54.547
but. then. boys will be boys.

694
00:30:54.618 --> 00:30:56.130
- Liz and Ressler?
- Not sure.

695
00:30:56.233 --> 00:30:59.137
I have... two other views.

696
00:30:59.256 --> 00:31:01.177
only one of any tactical value.

697
00:31:01.257 --> 00:31:02.002
It looks like they're in

698
00:31:02.059 --> 00:31:04.544
some sort of large
hand-built structure.

699
00:31:04.633 --> 00:31:05.420
Where?

700
00:31:05.508 --> 00:31:08.286
Funny you should ask--
in standby mode.

701
00:31:08.366 --> 00:31:12.466
the guidance systems ping GPS
coordinates every 30 seconds.

702
00:31:12.566 --> 00:31:14.194
- You ready?
- Go.

703
00:31:14.898 --> 00:31:17.571
[ Insects chirping ]

704
00:31:24.766 --> 00:31:26.796
Hey.

705
00:31:31.548 --> 00:31:33.358
Who are you?

706
00:31:38.203 --> 00:31:40.302
My name's Elizabeth.

707
00:31:43.138 --> 00:31:45.325
[ Branches cracking ]

708
00:32:18.668 --> 00:32:20.769
David: This isn't about me
or the others. father.

709
00:32:20.885 --> 00:32:24.257
This is about you--
your legacy. not mine!

710
00:32:24.462 --> 00:32:26.761
You think I haven't seen it?

711
00:32:29.115 --> 00:32:30.703
Read it?

712
00:32:31.467 --> 00:32:33.866
Prevarications and betrayals.

713
00:32:33.959 --> 00:32:35.471
Tell me who you are.

714
00:32:35.936 --> 00:32:36.948
Who's in charge?

715
00:32:37.032 --> 00:32:39.460
- Ken'yon.
- I want to talk to him.

716
00:32:39.534 --> 00:32:41.633
Only David talks to Ken'yon.

717
00:32:41.723 --> 00:32:43.276
You disgust me.

718
00:32:43.443 --> 00:32:45.916
Caleb:
David! David!

719
00:32:47.183 --> 00:32:48.511
What?

720
00:32:49.270 --> 00:32:49.978
What?!

721
00:32:50.055 --> 00:32:52.050
The prisoner wants
to talk to you.

722
00:33:01.618 --> 00:33:03.754
Caleb. watch the road.

723
00:33:04.013 --> 00:33:05.480
Make sure nobody else comes.

724
00:33:08.888 --> 00:33:10.281
Where are the others?

725
00:33:10.338 --> 00:33:13.405
Amy's safe.
along with the others.

726
00:33:13.487 --> 00:33:15.277
She's gonna be one of my wives.

727
00:33:15.836 --> 00:33:18.765
We're all gonna get married--
all of us.

728
00:33:19.096 --> 00:33:20.812
As prescribed by Ken'yon.

729
00:33:20.892 --> 00:33:23.558
And the man?
Ressler?

730
00:33:23.628 --> 00:33:25.462
What have you done with him?

731
00:33:43.161 --> 00:33:44.790
[ Grunts ]

732
00:33:47.844 --> 00:33:49.084
See?

733
00:33:49.468 --> 00:33:50.717
He's alive.

734
00:34:06.102 --> 00:34:07.458
Freeze!
Move away from him!

735
00:34:07.573 --> 00:34:08.952
Step away from him!

736
00:34:15.244 --> 00:34:16.684
I said freeze!

737
00:34:19.288 --> 00:34:20.713
Man: - Federal agents!
Man #2: - Get on the ground!

738
00:34:20.800 --> 00:34:22.615
[ Indistinct shouting ]

739
00:34:24.236 --> 00:34:25.967
- Let's go!
- Get on the ground!

740
00:34:26.076 --> 00:34:27.887
Don't move!
Show us your hands!

741
00:34:28.418 --> 00:34:29.419
Back off!

742
00:34:30.723 --> 00:34:32.157
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

743
00:34:32.269 --> 00:34:33.524
Kenyon's upstairs.

744
00:34:33.621 --> 00:34:35.285
Get this guy right here.
Get him out of here.

745
00:34:36.358 --> 00:34:37.525
He's gone.

746
00:34:46.992 --> 00:34:48.692
Kenyon.

747
00:34:51.127 --> 00:34:52.859
Stand down!
We found the...

748
00:34:55.528 --> 00:34:57.103
What?

749
00:34:57.944 --> 00:34:59.280
The third van.

750
00:35:09.370 --> 00:35:11.209
Get these kids out of here!

751
00:35:11.405 --> 00:35:13.647
See if you can locate
those missing girls.

752
00:35:13.730 --> 00:35:15.500
They've got to be
around here somewhere.

753
00:35:15.579 --> 00:35:16.999
- Call for backup.
- No backup!

754
00:35:17.133 --> 00:35:18.286
Just round up these kids

755
00:35:18.367 --> 00:35:20.360
with the personnel we've got
and clear out.

756
00:35:20.436 --> 00:35:21.823
Yes. ma'am.

757
00:35:23.630 --> 00:35:25.126
Don't come any closer!

758
00:35:25.194 --> 00:35:28.045
I've got 300 pounds
of explosives in this van!

759
00:35:30.245 --> 00:35:31.610
Go ahead.

760
00:35:32.538 --> 00:35:34.271
It's what he wanted. isn't it?

761
00:35:34.348 --> 00:35:35.287
What do you know?

762
00:35:35.361 --> 00:35:36.972
I know your father...

763
00:35:37.833 --> 00:35:39.697
wanted you dead.

764
00:35:42.528 --> 00:35:44.892
He sent us out there
to make us stronger.

765
00:35:45.022 --> 00:35:47.471
to be warriors.
to fulfill his prophecy!

766
00:35:47.538 --> 00:35:49.525
All those boys--

767
00:35:50.479 --> 00:35:52.637
they wouldn't have made it
if it weren't for you.

768
00:35:52.882 --> 00:35:56.315
taking them in.
teaching them how to survive.

769
00:35:56.510 --> 00:35:58.726
Your father never wanted them.

770
00:35:59.828 --> 00:36:01.697
He never wanted you.

771
00:36:02.984 --> 00:36:05.432
But you're not your father.
David.

772
00:36:06.478 --> 00:36:08.430
You're better than him.

773
00:36:12.103 --> 00:36:13.711
You're right.

774
00:36:15.868 --> 00:36:17.304
I am.

775
00:36:17.905 --> 00:36:19.214
Coward!

776
00:36:19.692 --> 00:36:20.733
[ Gunfire ]

777
00:36:51.813 --> 00:36:53.698
ATF's been over the grounds.

778
00:36:53.781 --> 00:36:55.068
They've searched
the buried containers.

779
00:36:55.155 --> 00:36:56.857
If you're wondering
about what you stored there.

780
00:36:57.022 --> 00:36:58.233
it's long gone.

781
00:36:58.312 --> 00:36:59.911
[ Drawer closes ]

782
00:37:02.454 --> 00:37:04.060
What's this?

783
00:37:04.146 --> 00:37:05.564
A key.

784
00:37:06.978 --> 00:37:09.782
I bought you an apartment
at the Audrey.

785
00:37:09.973 --> 00:37:13.824
top floor.
splendid view of the Potomac.

786
00:37:14.629 --> 00:37:16.046
Why?

787
00:37:16.154 --> 00:37:18.588
It's time to leave
the motel behind.

788
00:37:20.535 --> 00:37:21.761
[ Sighs ]

789
00:37:22.831 --> 00:37:24.927
I'm happy where I am.
Thank you.

790
00:37:26.584 --> 00:37:28.543
You've been many things
lately. Lizzy.

791
00:37:28.655 --> 00:37:30.428
but happy is not one of them.

792
00:37:30.530 --> 00:37:33.221
That motor lodge you call home
crushes the spirit.

793
00:37:33.321 --> 00:37:34.756
smothers the soul.

794
00:37:34.851 --> 00:37:37.684
And you think a view
is gonna change that?

795
00:37:39.132 --> 00:37:42.143
I once stayed
at a villa in Bali

796
00:37:42.301 --> 00:37:45.335
with a view
of the Indian Ocean.

797
00:37:46.024 --> 00:37:50.399
Every morning.
all I saw before me was...

798
00:37:51.933 --> 00:37:54.190
possibility.

799
00:37:56.592 --> 00:37:59.873
That and a gorgeous housekeeper
named Putu. who used to--

800
00:37:59.974 --> 00:38:01.759
Thanks. but. no. thanks.

801
00:38:05.189 --> 00:38:06.760
I wish you'd stop.

802
00:38:07.505 --> 00:38:08.750
Stop what?

803
00:38:08.881 --> 00:38:10.230
Trying.

804
00:38:10.295 --> 00:38:13.213
Stop hoping things are gonna
get better between us.

805
00:38:13.515 --> 00:38:15.811
You and me. it's just business.

806
00:38:16.562 --> 00:38:18.216
That's all it's ever gonna be.

807
00:38:24.782 --> 00:38:27.066
[ Crickets chirping ]

808
00:39:45.667 --> 00:39:47.789
♪<i> somewhere</i> ♪

809
00:39:48.350 --> 00:39:50.045
♪<i> beyond the sea</i> ♪

810
00:39:50.513 --> 00:39:53.666
♪ <i> somewhere waiting for me</i> ♪

811
00:39:55.199 --> 00:39:59.970
♪<i> my lover stands</i>
<i>on golden sands</i> ♪

812
00:40:00.059 --> 00:40:01.566
♪ and watches the ships ♪

813
00:40:01.659 --> 00:40:02.486
Tom: Single malt.

814
00:40:02.579 --> 00:40:05.853
- ♪ that go sailing ♪
- Highland. if memory serves.

815
00:40:05.982 --> 00:40:07.811
I got you in.

816
00:40:08.735 --> 00:40:10.103
♪ beyond the sea ♪

817
00:40:10.189 --> 00:40:11.635
Tom. I thought I was clear.

818
00:40:12.096 --> 00:40:14.288
I appreciate you thinking I'd be
a good Director. but--

819
00:40:14.370 --> 00:40:17.101
Screw the Director.
I got you into the trial.

820
00:40:17.834 --> 00:40:20.107
- At Georgetown.
- What?

821
00:40:20.996 --> 00:40:22.266
How?

822
00:40:22.378 --> 00:40:23.910
[ Chuckles ] Good questions.

823
00:40:24.522 --> 00:40:26.077
I know a guy who knows a guy.

824
00:40:26.452 --> 00:40:28.466
♪ it's far ♪

825
00:40:28.695 --> 00:40:29.536
[ Exhales lightly ]

826
00:40:29.649 --> 00:40:31.905
♪ beyond the stars ♪

827
00:40:31.981 --> 00:40:35.276
- ♪ it's near beyond the moon ♪
- Wait.

828
00:40:36.875 --> 00:40:38.351
Am I taking another
patient's spot?

829
00:40:38.436 --> 00:40:40.015
Because...
I couldn't accept that.

830
00:40:40.115 --> 00:40:41.127
That wouldn't be right.

831
00:40:41.248 --> 00:40:43.150
[ Laughs ]
Righteous to the end.

832
00:40:43.257 --> 00:40:44.561
Relax.

833
00:40:44.802 --> 00:40:47.337
It was going to be 35 patients.
and now it'll be 36.

834
00:40:47.514 --> 00:40:48.753
♪ we'll meet ♪

835
00:40:49.332 --> 00:40:51.792
♪ beyond the shore ♪

836
00:40:52.091 --> 00:40:54.519
♪ we'll kiss just as before ♪

837
00:40:54.584 --> 00:40:55.585
Thank you. Tom.

838
00:40:55.660 --> 00:40:56.639
[ Cork pops ]

839
00:40:56.758 --> 00:40:59.075
♪ happy we'll be
beyond the sea ♪

840
00:40:59.167 --> 00:41:00.646
There are good ships...

841
00:41:00.779 --> 00:41:02.363
and there are wood ships.

842
00:41:02.520 --> 00:41:04.599
The ships that sail the sea.

843
00:41:04.699 --> 00:41:06.185
But the best ships
are friendships.

844
00:41:06.270 --> 00:41:08.206
And may they always be.

845
00:41:08.496 --> 00:41:11.797
[<i> Instrumental break</i> ]

846
00:41:29.585 --> 00:41:32.075
♪<i> no more sailin'</i> ♪

847
00:41:32.474 --> 00:41:34.873
The number from the safe traces
to a blind exchange.

848
00:41:35.093 --> 00:41:37.560
We can't identify the party
you'll be speaking to.

849
00:41:52.632 --> 00:41:58.361
[ Dialing. line ringing ]

850
00:42:00.224 --> 00:42:01.714
Man: <i>Yes.</i>

851
00:42:05.748 --> 00:42:07.940
I'm calling on behalf
of Alan Fitch.

852
00:42:08.578 --> 00:42:11.926
<i>A safe.
You found the safe?</i>

853
00:42:13.897 --> 00:42:15.232
Who the hell is this?

854
00:42:18.537 --> 00:42:25.191
